# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Process Checklist (iteration gates)

This is the iteration loop — HOW each iteration runs. **It does not say WHAT to build: that is `PROJECT_PLAN.md` (the master checklist). Open the plan first; run these gates around every item you take from it.**

## First-run setup (for new contributors / new machines)

The canonical entry-point for "I just cloned this repo, how do I run it." A new contributor should be able to follow this and reach a green validator within minutes.

- [ ] Copy `.env.example` → `.env`, fill in values for the listed vars
- [ ] Install dependencies: `{{PKG_MANAGER}} install` (use the lockfile-honoring variant — `{{PKG_MANAGER}} ci` for npm, `--frozen-lockfile` for pnpm/yarn — when you want the exact recorded versions, per the lockfile-discipline rule)
- [ ] Run the project's setup script if one exists (check `package.json` `scripts.setup`, a `Makefile`'s `setup` target, or `scripts/setup`). If there is no setup script and one is needed for a new contributor to reach green, ADD ONE — "the setup command" is a contract every contributor depends on; an undocumented setup ritual is institutional knowledge that decays.
- [ ] Start the dev server: `{{DEV_SERVER_CMD}}`
- [ ] Run the validator once to confirm the baseline is green: `{{VALIDATOR_CMD}}`

If any of these fail on a fresh clone, that IS the work. Do not start any new feature on top of a broken setup.

## Iteration start (do not skip)

- [ ] Open `PROJECT_PLAN.md`. The next step is mechanical: the `Next action:` line = first unchecked item of the SINGLE active workstream (this iteration's work must be an item there — if it isn't, add it first). If nothing is active, picking the next item with the user IS the first task.
- [ ] Chore-debt check: in `PROJECT_PLAN.md` → Progress-triggered chores, verify no trigger fired without its chore running (lockfile changed since the commit in `Last ran at`? a milestone gate closed without calibration/review?). Fired-but-not-run chores are done FIRST this iteration.
- [ ] Run `{{VALIDATOR_CMD}}`. Tier 1 must be clean before any new work.
- [ ] Open {{TRUTH_SURFACE}} via {{TRUTH_SURFACE_TOOL}}. Write one sentence describing what it looks like right now.
- [ ] Spot-check drift surfaces: {{DRIFT_SURFACES}}.
- [ ] If a `plans/*/plan.md` is active (Status: active): re-read it top to bottom, plus the last 3 entries of `decision_log.md` (if generated) and the plan's `Discovered work` section. Then run a staleness check: for each file mentioned in the plan's open slices and recent decisions, verify the file still exists and was not modified after the plan's last update — if it was, do NOT start the planned action; re-plan first.

If any of the above is not green, **that** is the work. Do not start the next feature on top of a broken floor.

